    "body": "Thank you :)\n\n> I tracked this issue in my own config to the Command Duration config. In your config above:\n> \n> [cmd_duration]\n> show_milliseconds = true\n> format = \" in $duration \"\n> style = \"bg:lavender\"\n> disabled = false\n> show_notifications = true\n> min_time_to_notify = 45000\n> The issue is the `format` string contains a character not supported by the macOS notification font.\n> \n> You can fix this by restoring `format` to the default:\n> \n> format = \"took [$duration]($style) \"\n> It would be nice to have separate \"shell format\" and \"notification format\" strings that could be configured separately.\n\n",
